    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Up for sale is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54B32 3.2L inline-six engine. This high-revving powerplant utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear power band peaking at an 8,000 RPM redline. Shifting is handled via a crisp 6-speed Getrag manual transmission, sending power through a variable M differential lock for optimal corner-exit traction. This example features documented preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement and rear subframe reinforcement, ensuring structural and internal longevity. The suspension retains its factory-tuned damping characteristics, offering precise turn-in and high-speed stability. While the exterior shows minor patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the drivetrain remains tight and the hydraulic steering rack provides the unfiltered feedback characteristic of this chassis.",
